%S A397438 1,7,27,82,226,597,1545,3957,10080,25605,64944,164592,416961,1056051,
%T A397438 2674377,6772248,17148591,43422642,109951182,278407773,704955393,
%U A397438 1785012633,4519814580,11444577561,28978694784,73376640612,185796189153,470452483107,1191227527485,3016294014996,7637524595667,19338891204546,48967791568650
%N A397438 Growth function of the reflection group of a six-dimensional orthoscheme with distinct edge lengths.
%C A397438 A six-dimensional orthoscheme (path simplex) is a simplex with vertices V_0,...,V_6 whose edges V_0V_1, V_1V_2, ..., V_5V_6 are mutually perpendicular; here the six edge lengths are distinct positive rationals. W is the group generated by the reflections in the seven facets, and a(n) is the number of elements of W of word-length n in these reflections.
%C A397438 Two facets are perpendicular exactly when they are non-consecutive, so W is the right-angled Coxeter group with the path Coxeter diagram P_7; its growth series is given by Steinberg's formula, which yields the generating function and recurrence below.
%C A397438 The growth depends only on the perpendicularity pattern, not on the edge lengths. For dimension >= 3 the geometric orbit count equals this abstract growth for any distinct edge lengths (proved in the linked paper, using that distinct lengths force the consecutive dihedral angles irrational). The 2-dimensional analog is the right-triangle reflection group A396406. Verified by direct rational-arithmetic computation on edge lengths (1,2,3,5,7,11) through word-length 8.
%H A397438 Vico Bonfioli, <a href="https://github.com/ElVec1o/pythagorean-reflection-sequence">The Universal Right-Triangle Reflection Sequence (Unequal Legs)</a>, GitHub repository, 2026.
%H A397438 Vico Bonfioli, <a href="https://github.com/ElVec1o/pythagorean-reflection-sequence/blob/main/paper/journal/paper1b.pdf">Growth of n-dimensional orthoscheme reflection groups</a>, 2026.
%H A397438 Vico Bonfioli, <a href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.20370090">Data and proofs (Zenodo)</a>, doi:10.5281/zenodo.20370090, 2026.
%H A397438 <a href="/index/Rec#order_03">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (3,0,-3).
%F A397438 G.f.: (1 + x)^4 / (1 - 3*x + 3*x^3).
%F A397438 a(0)=1, a(1)=7, a(2)=27, a(3)=82, a(4)=226; a(n) = 3*a(n-1) - 3*a(n-3) for n >= 5.
%F A397438 a(n+1)/a(n) -> 1 + 2*cos(2*Pi/9) = 2.5320888..., the largest real root of x^3 - 3*x^2 + 3.
%e A397438 a(1) = 7: the seven reflections in the bounding facets are the 7 elements of word-length 1.
%t A397438 LinearRecurrence[{3, 0, -3}, {1, 7, 27, 82, 226}, 33]
%o A397438 (Python)
%o A397438 def aseq(N):
%o A397438     s = [1, 7, 27, 82, 226]
%o A397438     while len(s) < N:
%o A397438         s.append(3*s[-1] - 3*s[-3])
%o A397438     return s
%o A397438 print(aseq(33))
%Y A397438 Cf. A396406 (2D right-triangle reflection sequence, unequal legs).
%Y A397438 Cf. A397437 (4D analog) and A396927 (5D analog), same orthoscheme family.
%Y A397438 Cf. A008137 (3D all-equal-legs cube corner; affine Weyl group B~_3 growth series).
%K A397438 nonn,easy,new
%O A397438 0,2
